  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to comparatively assess the effectiveness of a tailored
      educational intervention to improve health literacy levels regarding upper respiratory
      infections (URIs) and to decrease pediatric emergency department (PED) visits, among Latino
      households in Early Head Start.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
